      public boolean startServerService​(int portNum, java.util.function.Function<java.lang.Boolean,​java.lang.Void> callback)
      Attemps to start ServerService with specified port num
      Expects a callback function with boolean value of whether the server is running
      Callback function can be empty if desired
      Parameters:
      portNum - port number to be used in the server
      callback - function accepting a Boolean value and returning null to be called when server was attempted to start
      Returns:

      Callback function always passes false, as server is not running
      Callback function can be empty if desired
      Parameters:
      callback - function accepting a Boolean value and returning null, to be called after server has been stopped
